{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863055830,"sessionID":"ses_286514219ffeo0SiZh53PR0xDV","part":{"id":"prt_d79afbba7001ffBAzs23plTVo5","messageID":"msg_d79afb2fe001ZeLOeDx4Ipkfrk","sessionID":"ses_286514219ffeo0SiZh53PR0xDV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4a0c4af5d5b74a0981870c67","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import \"time\"\n4: \n5: const (\n6: \tDefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n7: \tDefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n8: \tGCInterval                = 15 * time.Second\n9: \tGCSingleTickTimeout       = 2 * time.Minute\n10: \tDeleteTimeout             = 30 * time.Second\n11: )\n12: \n13: const (\n14: \tSessionIDLabelKey         = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n15: \tWorkloadNameLabelKey      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n16: \tSandboxNameLabelKey       = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n17: \tLastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"\n18: \tIdleTimeoutAnnotationKey  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n19: \tManagedByLabel            = \"managed-by\"\n20: \tManagedByValue            = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n21: )\n\n(End of file - total 21 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport \"time\"\n\nconst (\n\tDefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n\tDefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n\tGCInterval                = 15 * time.Second\n\tGCSingleTickTimeout       = 2 * time.Minute\n\tDeleteTimeout             = 30 * time.Second\n)\n\nconst (\n\tSessionIDLabelKey         = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n\tWorkloadNameLabelKey      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n\tSandboxNameLabelKey       = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n\tLastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"\n\tIdleTimeoutAnnotationKey  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n\tManagedByLabel            = \"managed-by\"\n\tManagedByValue            = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go","time":{"start":1775863055817,"end":1775863055829}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863055833,"sessionID":"ses_286514219ffeo0SiZh53PR0xDV","part":{"id":"prt_d79afc0db001fo9T6ZnLxjAliM","messageID":"msg_d79afb2fe001ZeLOeDx4Ipkfrk","sessionID":"ses_286514219ffeo0SiZh53PR0xDV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_619f84dd7b2e481890f9e4be","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the idle cleanup controller implementation for `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: IdleCleanupController interface\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `IdleCleanupController` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` with methods `Start(ctx context.Context) error`, `Stop()`, and `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)`. `CleanupResult` SHALL include `AgentRuntimesCleaned int`, `CodeInterpretersCleaned int`, and `Errors []CleanupError`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Start idle cleanup controller\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** a configured `IdleCleanupController` with `Enabled = true`\n16: - **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called during agentd initialization\n17: - **THEN** the controller SHALL start periodic cleanup cycles at `CleanupInterval` and watch resource events\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Stop controller gracefully\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a running `IdleCleanupController`\n22: - **WHEN** `Stop()` is called during shutdown\n23: - **THEN** the controller SHALL stop watching resources and complete in-flight cleanup operations\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Trigger immediate cleanup\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** idle resources exist exceeding configured timeouts\n28: - **WHEN** `CleanupNow(ctx)` is called manually\n29: - **THEN** an immediate cleanup cycle SHALL run and return `CleanupResult` with counts of cleaned resources\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Controller disabled\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.Enabled = false`\n34: - **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called\n35: - **THEN** the controller SHALL log \"Idle cleanup controller is disabled\" and return nil without starting watches or cleanup\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: CleanupResult with errors\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** cleanup encounters errors during deletion\n40: - **WHEN** `CleanupNow(ctx)` completes\n41: - **THEN** `CleanupResult.Errors` SHALL contain `CleanupError` entries for each failed resource\n42: \n43: ### Requirement: IdleTracker interface\n44: \n45: The system SHALL define `IdleTracker` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` with methods `UpdateLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string, timestamp time.Time)`, `GetLastActivity(kind, namespace, name string) (time.Time, bool)`, `IsIdle(kind, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) bool`, `Remove(kind, namespace, name string)`, and `ListIdleResources(timeout time.Duration) []ResourceKey`. `ResourceKey` SHALL include `Kind`, `Namespace`, and `Name` fields.\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Update last activity timestamp\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** an `IdleTracker` instance\n50: - **WHEN** `UpdateLastActivity(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", now)` is called\n51: - **THEN** the last activity for the resource SHALL be stored and retrievable via `GetLastActivity`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Check if resource is idle\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a resource with last activity 35 minutes ago\n56: - **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n57: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `true`\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Resource not yet idle\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** a resource with last activity 10 minutes ago\n62: - **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n63: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `false`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: No activity recorded\n66: \n67: - **GIVEN** a resource never had activity recorded via `UpdateLastActivity`\n68: - **WHEN** `IsIdle(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\", 30*time.Minute)` is called\n69: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `true` (treat as idle)\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: List all idle resources\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** multiple resources with varying last activity times\n74: - **WHEN** `ListIdleResources(30*time.Minute)` is called\n75: - **THEN** only resources idle for >= 30 minutes SHALL be returned\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Remove resource from tracking\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** a tracked resource in `IdleTracker`\n80: - **WHEN** `Remove(\"AgentRuntime\", \"default\", \"ar-1\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** the resource SHALL no longer appear in `ListIdleResources` or `GetLastActivity`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Thread-safe activity updates\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** concurrent calls to `UpdateLastActivity` from multiple goroutines\n86: - **WHEN** activity updates occur simultaneously\n87: - **THEN** all updates SHALL be applied correctly without data races\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: CleanupConfig structure\n90: \n91: The system SHALL define `CleanupConfig` in `pkg/agentd/config.go` with fields `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout time.Duration`, `CleanupInterval time.Duration`, `MaxConcurrentCleanups int`, `Enabled bool`, `DryRun bool`, `NamespaceAllowList []string`, and `NamespaceDenyList []string`. `DefaultCleanupConfig()` SHALL return config with AgentRuntime timeout 30m, CodeInterpreter timeout 15m, interval 5m, max concurrent 10, enabled true.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Default configuration values\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `DefaultCleanupConfig()` is called\n96: - **WHEN** the configuration is inspected\n97: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout` SHALL be `30 * time.Minute`\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Default CodeInterpreter timeout\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** `DefaultCleanupConfig()` is called\n102: - **WHEN** the configuration is inspected\n103: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Dry-run mode enabled\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.DryRun = true`\n108: - **WHEN** cleanup runs\n109: - **THEN** resources SHALL be logged but not deleted from the API server\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Namespace allow list filtering\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** `NamespaceAllowList = []string{\"default\", \"agents\"}`\n114: - **WHEN** cleanup evaluates a resource in namespace `\"other\"`\n115: - **THEN** the resource SHALL NOT be cleaned (namespace not allowed)\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Namespace deny list filtering\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** `NamespaceDenyList = []string{\"kube-system\", \"monitoring\"}`\n120: - **WHEN** cleanup evaluates a resource in namespace `\"kube-system\"`\n121: - **THEN** the resource SHALL NOT be cleaned (namespace denied)\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Max concurrent cleanups limit\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** `MaxConcurrentCleanups = 5` and 20 idle resources\n126: - **WHEN** cleanup cycle runs\n127: - **THEN** at most 5 deletion operations SHALL execute concurrently\n128: \n129: ### Requirement: Watch AgentRuntime resources\n130: \n131: The system SHALL implement `watchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context)` method that uses `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(metav1.NamespaceAll).Watch()` to monitor resource events. On `Added` or `Modified` events, update idle tracker with `Status.LastActivityTime` or `CreationTimestamp`. On `Deleted` events, remove from tracker.\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Watch receives Added event\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** a new AgentRuntime `\"ar-1\"` is created in namespace `\"default\"`\n136: - **WHEN** the watch receives the `Added` event\n137: - **THEN** `IdleTracker.UpdateLastActivity` SHALL be called with the resource's `CreationTimestamp`\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Watch receives Modified event with last activity\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with `Status.LastActivityTime` updated\n142: - **WHEN** the watch receives the `Modified` event\n143: - **THEN** `IdleTracker.UpdateLastActivity` SHALL be called with `LastActivityTime`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Watch receives Deleted event\n146: \n147: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime is deleted from the cluster\n148: - **WHEN** the watch receives the `Deleted` event\n149: - **THEN** the resource SHALL be removed from `IdleTracker`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Watch reconnection on failure\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** the watch connection fails\n154: - **WHEN** the watch channel closes\n155: - **THEN** the controller SHALL re-establish the watch with exponential backoff\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Watch context cancellation\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** the context is cancelled during shutdown\n160: - **WHEN** `ctx.Done()` is signaled\n161: - **THEN** the watch SHALL stop and call `watcher.Stop()`\n162: \n163: ### Requirement: Cleanup AgentRuntime resources\n164: \n165: The system SHALL implement `cleanupResource(ctx context.Context, kind, namespace, name string) error` that calls `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete()` with `GracePeriodSeconds: 30` and `PropagationPolicy: Foreground`. Metrics SHALL be recorded for duration and success/failure.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Delete idle AgentRuntime\n168: \n169: - **GIVEN** an idle AgentRuntime `\"ar-1\"` in namespace `\"default\"`\n170: - **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called for this resource\n171: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be deleted from the API server\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Delete with grace period\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** `cleanupResource` is called for an AgentRuntime\n176: - **WHEN** the delete operation executes\n177: - **THEN** `GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30 seconds\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Foreground propagation policy\n180: \n181: - **GIVEN** `cleanupResource` deletes an AgentRuntime\n182: - **WHEN** the delete options are set\n183: - **THEN** `PropagationPolicy` SHALL be `DeletePropagationForeground`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Cleanup non-existent resource\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime was already deleted by another process\n188: - **WHEN** `cleanupResource` attempts deletion\n189: - **THEN** a `NotFound` error SHALL be handled gracefully (logged, not retried)\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Dry-run skips deletion\n192: \n193: - **GIVEN** `CleanupConfig.DryRun = true`\n194: - **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called\n195: - **THEN** the method SHALL log the action but NOT call the delete API\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: Cleanup CodeInterpreter resources\n198: \n199: The system SHALL implement cleanup for CodeInterpreters using `agentClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()` with the same grace period and propagation policy as AgentRuntimes.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Delete idle CodeInterpreter\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** an idle CodeInterpreter `\"ci-1\"` in namespace `\"default\"`\n204: - **WHEN** `cleanupResource` is called for this resource\n205: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from the API server\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n208: \n209: - **GIVEN** `watchCodeInterpreters(ctx)` is running\n210: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created, modified, or deleted\n211: - **THEN** the `IdleTracker` SHALL be updated accordingly\n212: \n213: ### Requirement: CleanupMetrics\n214: \n215: The system SHALL define `CleanupMetrics` in `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` with Prometheus counters `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal`, `codeInterpreterCleanupsTotal`, `cleanupErrorsTotal`, histogram `cleanupDurationSeconds`, and gauge `idleResourcesDetected`. Methods SHALL include `RecordCleanup(kind string, duration time.Duration, err error)`, `SetIdleCount(kind string, count int)`, and `RecordError(kind string)`.\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Record successful cleanup\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime was successfully cleaned\n220: - **WHEN** `RecordCleanup(\"AgentRuntime\", 2*time.Second, nil)` is called\n221: - **THEN** `agentRuntimeCleanupsTotal` counter SHALL increment and duration histogram updated\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Record cleanup error\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter cleanup failed\n226: - **WHEN** `RecordCleanup(\"CodeInterpreter\", 1*time.Second, err)` is called\n227: - **THEN** `cleanupErrorsTotal` counter SHALL increment with kind label\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Set idle resource count\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** 15 idle AgentRuntimes detected\n232: - **WHEN** `SetIdleCount(\"AgentRuntime\", 15)` is called\n233: - **THEN** `idleResourcesDetected` gauge SHALL be set to 15\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Metrics exposed via Prometheus\n236: \n237: - **GIVEN** the metrics registry is registered with Prometheus\n238: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint is scraped\n239: - **THEN** all cleanup metrics SHALL be visible with proper labels\n240: \n241: ### Requirement: Namespace filtering\n242: \n243: The system SHALL implement `isNamespaceAllowed(namespace string) bool` method that checks deny list first, then allow list. System namespaces `kube-system` and `kube-public` SHALL be in the default deny list.\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Deny list takes precedence\n246: \n247: - **GIVEN** namespace `\"monitoring\"` is in both allow and deny lists\n248: - **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"monitoring\")` is called\n249: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `false` (denied)\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Empty allow list allows all\n252: \n253: - **GIVEN** `NamespaceAllowList` is empty\n254: - **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"any-namespace\")` is called for a non-denied namespace\n255: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `true`\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Default system namespace denial\n258: \n259: - **GIVEN** default configuration\n260: - **WHEN** `isNamespaceAllowed(\"kube-system\")` is called\n261: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `false`\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: Periodic cleanup cycle\n264: \n265: The system SHALL implement `runCleanup(ctx context.Context)` that runs at `CleanupInterval`, lists idle resources for both types, and cleans allowed namespaces concurrently respecting `MaxConcurrentCleanups`.\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Periodic cleanup execution\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** `CleanupInterval = 5 * time.Minute`\n270: - **WHEN** the controller is running\n271: - **THEN** `runCleanup` SHALL be invoked every 5 minutes\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Cleanup both resource types\n274: \n275: - **GIVEN** idle AgentRuntimes and CodeInterpreters exist\n276: - **WHEN** `runCleanup` executes\n277: - **THEN** both resource types SHALL be processed in the same cycle\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Concurrent cleanup with limit\n280: \n281: - **GIVEN** 50 idle resources and `MaxConcurrentCleanups = 10`\n282: - **WHEN** cleanup runs\n283: - **THEN** cleanup operations SHALL execute in batches of at most 10 concurrent deletions\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Cleanup cycle logs summary\n286: \n287: - **GIVEN** cleanup cycle completes\n288: - **WHEN** all operations finish\n289: - **THEN** a log message SHALL indicate number of resources cleaned and any errors\n290: \n291: ### Requirement: Environment variable configuration\n292: \n293: The system SHALL support configuration via environment variables: `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_DRY_RUN`, `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `AGENTD_CODE_INTERPRETER_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL`, `AGENTD_MAX_CONCURRENT_CLEANUPS`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST`, `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_DENY_LIST`.\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Load cleanup enabled from env\n296: \n297: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_ENABLED=false` is set\n298: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n299: - **THEN** `CleanupConfig.Enabled` SHALL be `false`\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Load idle timeout from env\n302: \n303: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_AGENT_RUNTIME_IDLE_TIMEOUT=1h` is set\n304: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n305: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeIdleTimeout` SHALL be `1 * time.Hour`\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: Load namespace allow list from env\n308: \n309: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_NAMESPACE_ALLOW_LIST=\"default,agents\"` is set\n310: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n311: - **THEN** `NamespaceAllowList` SHALL be `[]string{\"default\", \"agents\"}`\n312: \n313: #### Scenario: Invalid duration falls back to default\n314: \n315: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=invalid` is set\n316: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n317: - **THEN** the default interval SHALL be used and a warning logged\n318: \n319: ### Requirement: CleanupError types\n320: \n321: The system SHALL define `CleanupError` struct with fields `Type CleanupErrorType`, `ResourceKind string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`, `Message string`, and `Underlying error`. Error types SHALL include `CleanupErrorNotFound`, `CleanupErrorPermission`, `CleanupErrorTimeout`, `CleanupErrorConflict`, and `CleanupErrorUnknown`.\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: NotFound error handling\n324: \n325: - **GIVEN** resource is already deleted when cleanup attempts\n326: - **WHEN** API returns NotFound error\n327: - **THEN** `CleanupError.Type` SHALL be `CleanupErrorNotFound` and error is ignored\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Permission denied error\n330: \n331: - **GIVEN** RBAC does not allow delete on resource\n332: - **WHEN** cleanup attempts deletion\n333: - **THEN** `CleanupError.Type` SHALL be `CleanupErrorPermission` and logged for review\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Error string formatting\n336: \n337: - **GIVEN** a `CleanupError` with kind=\"AgentRuntime\", namespace=\"default\", name=\"ar-1\"\n338: - **WHEN** `Error()` is called\n339: - **THEN** the string SHALL include resource identification and error message\n340: \n341: ### Requirement: Graceful shutdown\n342: \n343: The system SHALL implement graceful shutdown in `Stop()` that closes `stopCh`, waits for in-flight cleanups via `sync.WaitGroup`, and logs shutdown completion.\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Stop closes stop channel\n346: \n347: - **GIVEN** a running controller\n348: - **WHEN** `Stop()` is called\n349: - **THEN** `stopCh` SHALL be closed signaling goroutines to exit\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Wait for goroutines to finish\n352: \n353: - **GIVEN** cleanup goroutines are running\n354: - **WHEN** `Stop()` is called\n355: - **THEN** the method SHALL block until all goroutines complete via `wg.Wait()`\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Shutdown logging\n358: \n359: - **GIVEN** controller shutdown completes\n360: - **WHEN** all goroutines exit\n361: - **THEN** a log message SHALL indicate \"Idle cleanup controller stopped\"\n362: \n363: ### Requirement: Integration with client-go\n364: \n365: The system SHALL use generated client-go from `deployment/client-go.md` including `versioned.Interface` for typed client access, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` for resource operations, and `watch.Interface` for event streaming.\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Create typed client for AgentRuntimes\n368: \n369: - **GIVEN** a configured `versioned.Interface` client\n370: - **WHEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\")` is called\n371: - **THEN** a typed `AgentRuntimeInterface` SHALL be returned for CRUD operations\n372: \n373: #### Scenario: Watch with typed client\n374: \n375: - **GIVEN** a typed `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n376: - **WHEN** `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})` is called\n377: - **THEN** a `watch.Interface` SHALL stream `Added`, `Modified`, `Deleted` events\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: List idle resources with label selector\n380: \n381: - **GIVEN** resources with various labels\n382: - **WHEN** `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=test\"})` is called\n383: - **THEN** only matching resources SHALL be returned for idle evaluation\n384: \n385: ## Dependencies\n386: \n387: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n388: |------------|--------|-------|\n389: | `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Kubernetes client interfaces |\n390: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated | Typed client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n391: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Generated | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types |\n392: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch` | External | Watch event streaming |\n393: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | External | Metadata, deletion options |\n394: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n395: | `prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` | External | Metrics exposition |\n396: | `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | External | Concurrent cleanup with limits |\n397: \n398: ## Files to Create/Modify\n399: \n400: | File | Action | Description |\n401: |------|--------|-------------|\n402: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` | Create | IdleCleanupController interface and implementation |\n403: | `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` | Create | IdleTracker interface and implementation |\n404: | `pkg/agentd/config.go` | Create | CleanupConfig structure and loading |\n405: | `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics.go` | Create | Prometheus metrics for cleanup |\n406: | `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for cleanup controller |\n407: | `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for idle detection |\n408: | `pkg/agentd/config_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for configuration |\n409: | `pkg/agentd/cleanup_metrics_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for metrics |\n410: \n411: ## Testing Strategy\n412: \n413: 1. **Unit Tests**: Mock client-go interfaces, test idle detection logic, verify namespace filtering\n414: 2. **Integration Tests**: Use fake clientset from `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/`, test full cleanup flows\n415: 3. **Concurrent Tests**: Verify thread-safety of IdleTracker under concurrent access\n416: 4. **Error Injection Tests**: Use reactors on fake client to test error handling paths\n\n(End of file - total 416 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the idle cleanup controller implementation for `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: IdleCleanupController interface\n\nThe system SHALL define `IdleCleanupController` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` with methods `Start(ctx context.Context) error`, `Stop()`, and `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)`. `CleanupResult` SHALL include `AgentRuntimesCleaned int`, `CodeInterpretersCleaned int`, and `Errors []CleanupError`.\n\n#### Scenario: Start idle cleanup controller\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured `IdleCleanupController` with `Enabled = true`\n- **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called during agentd initialization\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL start periodic cleanup cycles at `CleanupInterval` and watch resource events\n\n#### Scenario: Stop controller gracefully\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863055820,"end":1775863055830}}}}
